.TH plfs_chown 3 "${PACKAGE_STRING}" 
.SH NAME
plfs_chown 
.SH SYNTAX
#include <plfs.h>
.PP
int plfs_chown( const char *path, uid_t, gid_t );

.SH DESCRIPTION
Change ownership of a PLFS file.  See chown(2) for more details.

.SH INPUT PARAMETERS
.TP 1i
path
File to change ownership
.TP 1i
uid_t
owner
.TP 1i
gid_t
group

.SH RETURN VALUES
Most PLFS functions return 0 or -errno, except write and read
which return the number of bytes or -errno

